Retrospective study on PET-SPECT imaging in a large cohort of myotonic dystrophy type 1 patients. The aim was to study brain involvement in myotonic dystrophy type 1 by single photon emission tomography (SPECT) and positron emission tomography (PET). 58 DM1 patients were subjected to SPECT 17 to both SPECT and PET. SPECT patients were grouped as 'normally perfused' and 'abnormally perfused'